This paper involves the development of a real-time music improvisation system using process calculi and probabilistic models. The use of process calculi and probabilistic models suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The development of a real-time system suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The use of concurrent constraint programming suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
